27.8. Legends for Printouts

  


Requirements

Sean Miller 04/29/2025: Moved to [[[IN11426](https://zch.apphosting.zone/Detail/Edit/2?RecordType=Incidents&NumberID=-11428&)]] - ZGW - Legends for Printouts

  


  


The Phase 1 spec initially included legends for Species and Grade at the bottom of some of the printout templates. These are being removed in interest of reducing scope & cost, but can be added in if desired.

  


Printouts affected:

  * Buyer Invoice Printout
  * Delivery Ticket Printout page



  


Legends included:

  * Species (abbreviation and possibly full name)
  * Lumber Grades (variety of abbreviations and full names)



  


Estimated Cost: TBD (depending on what approach is used, etc.)

  


Spec: The legends could be implemented in a variety of ways, and the exact visual format on the printout also could vary. Following are a few options:

  


  * Display a table or list of items, based on the current / active records in the Solution (this is the most likely implementation). 
  * Display a hard-coded table or list of items.
  * Display a user-configurable list of items, based on multi-line plain text fields on the Silverloom Settings page.



  


Development Specification

  * Buyer Invoice Printout | Legends (if legends are included):
    * Grades: Displays a table of active "Grade Names", in alphabetical order.
  * Delivery Ticket Printout Page | Legends (if legends are included):
    * Grades: Displays a table of active Lumber Grade "Grade Names", in alphabetical order.



  


List example for Species: "Species: BE = Beach, HK = Hickory, HM = Hard Maple, PO = Poplar, RO = Red Oak, SM = Soft Maple, WA = Walnut, WO = White Oak"

List example for Grade: "Grades: 1C, 2C, 3C, FAS, F1F, Quartered, Rift, Rustic, Veneer"
